text: Cheng I-ching (; born 15 February 1992) is a Taiwanese table tennis player. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's singles event, in which she was eliminated in the quarterfinals by Li Xiaoxia, and as part of the Chinese Taipei team in the women's team event. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Taiwanese female table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of Taiwan Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Universiade medalists in table tennis Category:Table tennis players at the 2010 Asian Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2014 Asian Games Category:World Table Tennis Championships medalists Category:Table tennis players at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Universiade silver medalists for Chinese Taipei Category:Asian Games competitors for Chinese Taipei Category:Expatriate table tennis people in Japan Category:Medalists at the 2013 Summer Universiade Category:Medalists at the 2015 Summer Universiade Category:Medalists at the 2017 Summer Universiade
